animal.description:
Hi I'm Bailey and I'll be 2 in April. They say I'm a lab hound mix, and something about probably a beagle. All I know is I'm super cute and it gets me all kinds of belly rubs (which I like even more than treats, and definitely more than kibble)!

I'm a quick learner, but I like to have things my way. I'll definitely let you know when I want something... I'm sweet but very persistent.

I don't like big noises, and when I'm scared I forget everything I know. I'm still not sure what to think of this city life... My foster mom says we live in a pretty quiet neighborhood, but I'm not convinced. It's getting less scary every day, though, and the apartment is super cozy! I felt at home right away, even if the outside world is a bit overwhelming.

I definitely miss my family in IN. I had 4 human siblings and one doggie big sis. They said I was a lot of energy for her, though, and they were always super busy so I spent a lot of the day in a crate.

Sometimes I do get the zoomies, but I only let them out in the yard - I'd really like a place with plenty of space to run and play. And it would be real nice to have a family to love on me again! For now my foster mom and I get along great, and I especially like that she made a spot for me where I could see out the window all day.

If you are interested in adopting Bailey, please fill out an application at:
https://www.dogsaredeservingrescue.com/adoptable-dogs/adoption-application/

animal.description:
Blondie is a precious 12-year-old senior female Pomeranian that weighs 9 pounds. She has a great personality and gets along great with everyone! She enjoys the company of other dogs, doesn't mind cats, and has no issues with children. She is a total lovebug that just wants to be your shadow and follow you around the house. Despite her age, she's a spunky girl that we hope has many years ahead of her. She does great on a harness/leash, rides well in the car, and is the perfect buddy to take naps with. You can tell Blondie was once potty trained, but due to her age, it can be difficult for her to make it outside in time. She uses potty pads which is great! Blondie's bloodwork indicated slightly elevated kidney levels, but that is pretty common for senior dogs. She is spayed, vaccinated, heartworm negative, had a ProHeart 6 shot, and microchipped. She is $250 plus TX sales tax with an approved application: www.recycledpomsbcs.com/adopt

Texas law requires that all humane organizations (Rescues, SPCA's, Humane Societies, State nonprofit, and charitable 501c3 exempt orgs) collect and remit sales and use tax to the Texas Comptroller on their adoption fees.

We do not ship or transport our dogs. We require all adopters to meet the dog in person to ensure it is a good fit. We represent the dog to the best of our ability and since they are in rescue, we do not always get their history.

Please note: We are a non-profit Pomeranian Rescue with dogs in private foster homes. We do not have a facility open to the public. We require an approved application before a potential adopter is introduced to a dog. We contact vet references to ensure animals in the home are current on vaccinations, heart worm prevention, and sterilization. We do not adopt our dogs to homes in which an animal is not spayed or neutered. A home visit may be required.

Please visit our website for more information and an adoption application. www.recycledpomsbcs.com

animal.description:
Canelo is a handsome 5.5 year old Chihuahua/Basenji mix who is looking for a loving forever home. He weighs about 12 pounds and is full grown. Canelo has quite the personality and will make a wonderful pup for the right family/person, but he will need a family that is the perfect fit! Prior to coming to us in June 2020, Canelo had sadly spent most of his life outside and if he was ever in trouble, he was punished by not receiving affection or attention. Since being with us, he has been spoiled, loved, and has spent some time in foster homes too! Canelo warms up to gentle affection from those he trusts, but is understandably timid and standoffish with new people at first. Canelo will need a patient and loving family of adults over 18 only. Canelo loves the attention of those he trusts and can be a lap guarder towards other dogs, so he would be happiest as the only pet. However, he does love to play with certain dogs and may do well with another dog that is playful and is not a big human cuddler (dog intro required). Canelo loves to play, especially with toys and would love an active home with plenty of toys! He is great on leash and would be a perfect running or hiking buddy. He is housebroken, and knows how to use the dog door too! He is a quiet boy, only alerting when someone is at the door. Canelo was used to spending too much time outside, but is still used to having a yard to run in so he will need a home with a yard or a condo with a yard, no apartments please. Canelo can be a digger if left alone in the yard and bored, so he will need to be watched to make sure he doesn't do too much gardening. He is a sweet boy, whom with a bit of patience, will be an affectionate, snuggly, and loving boy to his person/people. He is neutered, up to date on vaccines, vet checked and microchipped. His adoption fee is $160 which includes a complimentary vet visit. To potentially adopt him, please bring everyone living in the home 2 legged and 4 to our shelter location at 1102 W Hatcher Rd in Phoenix 85021, open Tuesday to Sunday 11am to 6pm. --Covid update: To adhere to CDC guidelines, we are open for adoptions only at a max capacity of 15 people in the building at a time. Masks/face coverings are required. For the safety of our staff and customers, we ask that you practice social distancing, sanitization, and if exposed to Covid-19 or sick to please stay home.--

animal.description:
Introducing a puppy so cute, it might be a felony! 

Alcapone wants to join your family's gang and steal your heart with his puppy breath and adorable face. This little guy was born in December 2020 and is expected to be med/large when full grown. 

Please note: as with most rescue puppies, we have no way to guarantee this puppy’s breed or size potential. 

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

The adoption fee for adult dogs covers age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, spay/neuter if not yet performed, heartworm test & appropriate heartworm treatment by the rescue's vet. All dogs in our care are also kept up-to-date on HW/Flea Prevention. Please see our website for more information. 

2021 Adoption Fee Scale for non-benefactor animals:
Puppies under 12 months - $300
Dogs over 12 months - $200

For additional information, including the adoption process and our adoption fee scale for all our adoptable pets, see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

*Any breed labels used by Take Paws Rescue, its employees/volunteers, or on vet records provided cannot be guaranteed.  Breed labels are given based on information obtained during intake and/or best guesses based on appearance and/or temperament of the dogs and Take Paws Rescue gives no assurance to the accuracy of these labels. Labels are necessary for postings to many animal networking sites, such as Pet Finder, and are no way a guarantee. Additionally, exact age and potential size cannot be guaranteed.

animal.description:
The wonderful Walker weighs 46 pounds and is estimated to be between the age of 1-3 years old.  He is the cutest!

This boy is so darn happy, his tail never quits wagging.  What to say about Walker, except that he is awesome and he would make such a great best friend. He enjoys ear rubs and closeness, he just leans in for snuggles.  He does pretty good on a leash for a hound too, it is very sweet, he likes to "check in" with you to get a pet, then back to sniffing he goes.  As you can see in the picture of him in the snow, he just wanted a little love before he continued!  Walker does love the sound of his own voice though, so you will have to like his baying as well!  

Walker does need an experienced adopter who is knowledgeable of the breed.  This nice boy needs to be taught a few manners too, he can be a bit of a counter surfer and needs work on jumping up for attention.  He is super sweet, but may be too much for young kids. Walker will also need some type of yard containment, with his houndy nose, we want to keep him safe.  

We have exciting news to share about Walker and 3 other dogs at our rescue. They are participating in a Teacher's Pet program in which they travel twice a week to Crossroads, an at youth risk center, and are paired with a youth. They will be working with our pups on some obedience training and giving them some much needed one on one time. What a wonderful program, we are so happy about it and thrilled for our dogs.

If you are interested in Walker and are at least 21 years old, please fill out an application and we will be in touch.

Donate at codysfriendsrescue.org to help us save more lives! https://codysfriendsrescue.org/donate

This friendly and sweet-natured fellow is Chip, a Lab mix who was brought to a local Animal Shelter on 9/12 with injuries. Chip is approximately 4 years old, weighs 45 pounds Chip was seen by a vet who diagnosed him to have sustained attack wounds with large degree of infection on all four legs, the most substantial on the left elbow. His one leg never healed from all the infection so we had to amputate his leg. He acts like iit doesn't bother him at all!!!. Chip doesn't seem depressed or unhappy with his situation. He is a sweet and happy boy. He is heart worm positive which we are treating. Chip is a dog who has not been well cared for -he came in covered in fleas as well which we treated. It is so sad that Chip was not cared for by his owners and so sad that Chip is having to pay for it with his health but he is on his way to recovery and iis ready for adoption! . He walks well on a leash, is house broken, and likes to play in the yard. He takes treats gently and knows the sit command. He loves to play with other dogs.

animal.description:
This may be a tad biased because Marlins foster absolutely loves him. He needs an extra special and patient home to help him be the best version of himself 

Dog Name: Marlin

Breed: Hound

Sex: Male (Neutered)

Age: 1 1/2 Years 

Weight: 35lb

Medical Needs: None

Housebroken: Yes

Crate trained: Yes, goes right in for treats. Will sleep through the night in his crate and the foster will put him in for quiet time when he get gets overexcited

Good in the car: No, becomes over anxious and will bark at everything he sees. Has vomited in the car before, most likely due to anxiety. 

Good on a leash: Loves to go for walks and smell everything, but quite a strong puller. He has a harness that will go with him. 

Energy level: High. Will need daily walks and fetch sessions with the tennis ball, plus toys and puzzles to keep his brain and body busy. 

Need a fenced in yard: Yes, likes to gallop around like a horse to burn off that energy. 

Dog Friendly: Yes - but must be similiar energy level & temperament. Was not taught proper play as a puppy and can be quite overwhelming. 

Does your foster need another dog in its adoptive homes?
Not necessary, would be happy to be getting all the attention as an only.

Cat Friendly? Unsure

Kid Friendly: NO. Marlin was never taught proper play or received any training as a puppy, as a result he has no manners and his play style is very aggressive. He will jump and mouth for attention or while playing, and will need a patient foster to work on correcting these behaviors. 

Special traits that make your foster special or that we need to know about them?
Sweet, special Marlin his foster family loves to snuggle up with him on the couch and pet his velvety ears. He could play fetch for hours and loves to explore nature with his inquisitive hound nose. He has already learned sit stay release (the tennis ball) and is learning that mouthing human hands is not how to get attention. His adopter must be dog savvy and ready to put in the work to provide the training he was never given while younger. When Marlin gets proper exercise and stimulation, he will happily nap next to his people on the couch.

animal.description:
Hello! My name is Ziggy and I'm a special little guy who is looking for a special home. I'm a smaller/medium sized dog who is about 30 pounds. When I came to the shelter, I was kind of a wreck with really horrible ear infections, bad teeth (I had to have 18 of them pulled!), a tick-borne illness that needed to be treated and some bad skin. Whew! That's a lot. Thankfully, I've been all taken care of and life is just great! 

I'm a very happy dog who loves to go for short walks, but doesn't demand a lot of exercise or playtime. I am just as happy snuggling up with my people. 

I am deaf or mostly deaf, but I don't let it bother me. Hey, it helps me sleep really well since I can't hear the noise around me. :) I get along with most other dogs and I am good with kids that are out of the toddler stage and will respect me. 

If you are looking for an older dog who would just love to be your very best friend in the world, please apply for me!

animal.description:
Stanley is a 50 lb, 5 yr old, Border Collie mix. He was rescued from a hoarding situation in Nebraska. He is very shy and would do better with another confident resident dog. We don't forsee cats being an issue. Small children will be too stressful for Stanley. He needs a fenced in yard. He is slowly making progress in the shelter environment but he really needs to develop and gain self confidence in a home. He is very sweet. Stanley will need a home that will take time and patience to work with him, this will not be an overnight success story. We can promise you it will be worth all your hard work and patience!! We will assist you with advice and with anything you need to be successful. We don't feel house training will be a problem due to he holds it at the shelter. Due to Stanley being so matted he needed to be shaved so we have a coat on him for now to keep him warm outside. He tends to spend alot of time in the outside run. Once his coat grows out he will be more handsome than he is now. Our pleasant boy Stanley is a diamond in the ruff! We guarantee he will become a very loving family pet. If you think you would like to assist Stanley flourish in your household please contact us. 

The adoption fee is $300 and covers age propriate vaccines, a microchip, and a spay/neuter.

 Applications are typically worked in time stamp order based on date/time of submission. If you have other dogs in your home, they must all meet the potential adoptee. It may save you a trip to bring them with you when you visit, if you are certain you want to adopt a new family member. 

*****We are currently operating by appointment only during the social distancing stage of quarantine. If you want to meet this pet, or are interested in adopting, please submit an inquiry or email to email@townandcountryhumanesociety.org.

Someone from the rescue will contact you and/or your family and determine, on a broad level, whether you might be a fit for the animal. If so, they will provide instructions for completing the application. Your application will be reviewed and you will be contacted to set up a time to meet at the shelter or the foster home. The introduction between you and the pet will be supervised by one of the dog counselors or the foster. If all goes well, you can adopt during the same visit.

Please be sure to follow us on Facebook to learn more about Town and Country Humane Society and our mission.

animal.description:
All dogs adopted through Troy Animal Rescue Project are up to date on vaccinations, spayed/neutered (age appropriate), and heartworm negative. All dogs are given monthly flea/tick preventative, monthly heartworm preventative, and are dewormed regularly. Dogs adopted through Troy Animal Rescue Project are microchipped. Adoption fee is $50. Home visit and vet reference required. Applications can be put in online at http://www.troyanimalrescueproject.org/adopt.php or in person at our rescue center.

The address for our rescue center is 34 County Road 2266, Brundidge, AL 36010. We are one turn off Hwy 167. If you use Google maps, type in Troy Animal Rescue Project and it will take you right to us. Hours of operation are from 10-3 daily. We are open Saturdays and Sundays. No appointment necessary for pets that are located at the rescue center. Appointments must be made to visit pets in foster homes. Location information will be listed beside the pets name if they are at a location other than our rescue center.

Questions can be emailed to troyanimalrescueproject@gmail.com or call 334-508-2367.

animal.description:
*Please read the full bio*
If you are interested in meeting me , we require an approved application. If you have questions regarding adoption, please visit our website --> www.adoptionfirstanimalrescueky.com
Please do not email us asking if the dog is available. We will not respond to emails that can be answered on our website.
*MEDICAL DISCLOSURE* Knox was brought into the vet at 5 weeks old unable to process food, he would regurgitate it. We did a work up, and radiologist said Knox had PRAA. Several months later, we scheduled surgery and did new Xrays, and a barium swallow. The barium passed straight through, and doctors do not think he needs surgery. Knox does have to eat wet food only, on a raised feeder. His issues seems to have resolved itself, but may need attention in the future. You must agree and discuss this with us as it requires financial stability.
Hey guys! My name is Knox I am a 3 month old German Shepherd mix, my foster momma says I am the best boy. I love to play with the other doggies in my house but the kitties are boring, so I just ignore them. I've had some issues with food so my foster mommy has used blueberries and bananas when we have my special training time. They are super yummy and my absolute favorite! My foster says I'm a super quick learner too. I've learned a bunch of basic commands and am almost potty trained. I would love it if I could find my forever family. I'm a snuggly boy and just want someone that is gonna love me forever. NO apartments, condos, or townhomes. MUST have a 6 foot privacy fence.
Complete Application
You must complete the adoption application in full to be considered for adoption.
Home Check
All adoptions do require a home check. If you are not comfortable with a home check please do not apply. We want to ensure the safety of our dogs and to make sure the adoptive family is comfortable.
Meet and Greet
If your application has been approved we will schedule a meet and greet for the dog of your choice or for a few we think might be a good fit for your family.
Sign Adoption Contract
This must be read and signed prior to adoption.
Adoption Fee
Once everything has been reviewed the adoption fee will need to be paid. Puppies under 6 months is $300, over 6 months is $250, over 10 years is $150. Adoption fee includes: -Spay or Neuter -Microchip (additional registration fee required to transfer ownership to adopters) -Up to date on vaccinations -All animals have been examined by a veterinarian ** All adoption fees are non refundable.

animal.description:
Hello there!  We are Baby and Chilita and we are 9 and 8 years old respectively.  Baby is Chilita's mom and they have been together their entire lives so they will need to be adopted together.  Our adoption fee is $180 for the pair.  We are spayed, up to date on our vaccines, and microchipped.  We came to the shelter because our owner had to move and sadly where he was moving, does not accept pets.  We love each but we would prefer to be the only dogs in the house.  We did previously live with a cat so we may be alright sharing our space with a feline friend.  We are housebroken but occasionally have an accident if no one is paying attention that we need to go outside.  We perform the "Rottweiler lean" like nobody's business.  We both love people and may push each other out of the way to see who can get the most pets.  We are happy to share space with each other.  Baby loves stuffed toys and that she does not always want to share with Chilita but Chilita is very respectful to Baby and does not try and take a toy from her.  We do groom each other and will often lick each other's faces.  We have been excellent at the shelter and are often up in the office.  We have loved everyone we have met and have even been quite the perfect ladies during our vet exams.

We are senior ladies and have what you would expect as far as senior large breed dog issues.  We have arthritis and some lumps and bumps that may need to be removed.  We are such loving dogs and true representatives of what the Rottweiler breed should be.  (Chilita has her tail so there is even more of her to love.)  We are hoping that someone's heart is big enough to give these girls the home they deserve in their golden years.
animal.name: Baby & Chilita

animal.description:
Say hello to Chica! She's a 3.5 year old Chihuahua/Australian Shepard mix who has just joined her Muddy Paws foster family. Despite her small stature, Chica has a big personality and knows how to run the show! She grew up in a household with two large breed dogs and made sure they knew who was boss! Chica is now living with two small dogs in her foster home and we're glad to report that everyone is getting along just peachy. First impressions are that Chica is a smart, friendly little thing who is very treat motivated (hello, rotisserie chicken!), knows how to potty outside, can jump really high, knows some tricks, and is already smitten with her foster mom. Nestling into soft blankets for lots of snuggles makes this gal pretty happy! We're anticipating lots of entertaining updates about Chica and will know more about her furever home "wish list" over the next few weeks!

The suggested adoption donation for Chica is $350. We are a 501c3 organization which means that your donation may be TAX DEDUCTIBLE. Your donation goes toward the high cost of veterinary care for our animals in rescue, as well as providing supportive services to animals in homes. 

Information about the adoption process: All adoptions require a completed ADOPTION APPLICATION. Once your application is approved, we will put you in touch with the dogs foster to see if you and the pet are a good match. If so, we will arrange a meeting for you and the pet. The adoptions for all of our animals will take place in the Omaha, NE area and must be done by the adoptive family in person. We do not ship or deliver. 

Please Note: We are a RESCUE, which is different from a shelter. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We always select the right applicant for each dog, based on the dogs needs. If you and the dog are not a good match, we will help you select another dog, or we will keep your approved application on file for 6 months. 

To learn about Muddy Paws Second Chance Rescue or donate to our animals, please visit our website at MuddyPawsSecondChanceRescue.com or our Facebook Page.

**WE ARE ALWAYS IN NEED OF FOSTER HOMES**  Homeward Bound Dog Rescue is an all volunteer rescue organization and all our dogs and puppies are in foster homes - we are not a shelter and do NOT have a facility where we house our dogs. For adoption information go to: www.homewardbounddogrescue.com.  You must fill out an application online as we do NOT accept applications at our clinics.

Hi, I am Rocco, a male Lab mix, 12 years old and 44 lb.  I walk extremely well on a leash and am housebroken. I am a sweet boy who loves it when you love on me, and I don't like being alone, but when I am, I am not destructive.  I do have a tendency to bark when I am alone.  I am a big guy but I want to be a lap dog. I am fine around other dogs.  All I really want is a place to be safe, warm and loved, is that so much to ask?

We are presently not holding our regular Saturday adoption clinics due to the Covid-19 virus.  We are operating on a limited basis until further notice, but we are still adopting dogs out. We require an approved application before we consider anyone for an adoption - so filling out the application is your first step.   Different dogs and puppies go up for adoption EVERY WEEK so please feel free to visit the site and click on the Petfinder link for updates. Puppies and dogs up to 2 years old are $350. Dogs over 2 years old are $250. 100% of the adoption fees go to help us save more dogs.

Due to the high number of emails we receive, we are unable to respond to general inquiries. 
If interested in adopting, please apply on our website, www.luckytalesrescue.org. As long as the pet is viewable, we are accepting applications. No matter the outcome, we will email all applicants once the pet has been adopted. Thank you for your understanding.

**

Hi I’m Buddy and smiling is my favorite thing! I look like a big boy here, but at 6 months old I'm only 35 lbs. My foster mom thinks I’m the sweetest boy. I'll admit it -- she's 100% right. I love people of all sizes, so I'm glad that I live with 4 small ones right now and I am great with them. I have two siblings, one is very floofy, and the other is not, but I am the least floofy of all. Lucky Tales thinks I may be Lab mixed with some Great Pyrenees or maybe Collie. 

I'm also really good with cat friends and I will play all day with other dogs. I like to play tug in the backyard and chase my dog friend around and around. When I'm done being dizzy and come inside from playing, I will lay on my back for you to wipe me down. It's like a mini spa treatment.... ahhhh!

In case you haven't picked up on it yet, I'm very smart. I already learned how to sit, shake, and lay down. I am crate trained and house trained, too. I love to chew on toys and make them squeak! If it was up to me, I would lay on the couch all day and take a nap with my head in your lap. Please give me a home I love you, I love you, I loooveee youuuu!

I am up to date on vaccinations, microchipped, heartworm negative, and neutered. 
My adoption fee is $300?

animal.description:
Buddy: ~10-month-old male yellow Lab/Husky mix ~70 lbs soon to be neutered

Background: 
This sweet boy was originally a gift to a college student, who has realized that, much as he loves him, he does not have the time to give Buddy the attention and training he needs.  So his family contacted Lab Rescue for help in finding Buddy his forever home.

What Buddy’s owner says:
Buddy is a great dog and companion. He is very affectionate and loves to be with our family as much as possible. He is potty trained and sleeps in our home every night.   He also loves hanging out indoors with us during the day when we are around.   His favorite thing is to play outdoors.  He loves to walk, run and play with other dogs.  He also gets a great workout and has a lot of fun fetching tennis balls.   After a good workout, Buddy enjoys being washed and blow dried as well.  On a final note, one of his favorite things to do is to have me share my rotisserie chicken with him (of course in moderation).  In summary, whoever is fortunate enough to have Buddy as part of their journey in life will be filled with much love and joy. 


What Buddy’s Rescue Rep says: 
Buddy is a super sweet, energetic young pup with all that entails! Upon first meeting Buddy, he jumped up and was a bit reserved and distant and not real sure about what was going on. Like many young dogs adopted during the pandemic, the opportunities to socialize him with humans and the outside world have been limited. 

He’s had some training and knows Sit, Down, Wait (all of which he does well), Stay, Come and Leave It (these are harder, and he could use more practice). He takes treats incredibly gently, loves to play fetch, did well with his food guarding and handling evals, and is super playful. He does jump up on you, and is still very mouthy, but he’s eager to please and can learn to not engage in these behaviors.  He loves to go on walks (probably because they often end at the dog park, where he also loves to play with other dogs and to run….and run….and run!). 
One of his most endearing habits is to take the leash in his mouth at the beginning of the walk, as if to say “let’s go, let’s go!”. He walks on a martingale collar and while he pulls, he does settle down after a bit. At the dog park he meets other dogs well, runs with them, bounces around and generally enjoys himself while burning off some of that puppy energy (the walk home is much better!). If a dog engages in behavior that makes Buddy uncomfortable, he disengages.  Check out these brief snippets of Buddy in action:


Buddy starts a Walk - https://youtu.be/SBdpbfN8oLI

Buddy walking calmly - https://youtu.be/2jn4m5hQpss

Buddy at the Dog Park - https://youtu.be/VAvkj-Yf8v8

Buddy meets dogs - https://youtu.be/FVbXE70F9xo

Buddy Follows Dad - https://youtu.be/dmkW3CsZU3M

Buddy Walks Home - https://youtu.be/2QRmEn2d0HE

We’d like Buddy to go to a home with an experienced adopter who can help Buddy become the wonderful companion dog he is capable of being. Buddy is in the teenage stage of puppyhood, with all that entails (learn more about teenage dogs here:  https://www.sciencemag.org/news/2020/05/dogs-get-difficult-when-they-reach-adolescence-just-human-teenagers) but is eager to learn and to please. 
Buddy is a high energy dog that will need at least an hour of vigorous exercise and play each day (a tired dog is a good dog!). Currently he’s accustomed to a daily walk and/or dog park visit, so that’s what he will expect from his new home! This will also help with training; after a good run or game of fetch Buddy will be more relaxed and able to pay attention to his training. He’ll need lots of chew and play toys to keep him occupied throughout the day.

Buddy has not been exposed to small children, and given his size and energy level, his new home should not have children under the age 13. 

He has been around cats and done well (he has always been supervised when the cats are around). Buddy would be fine as an only dog in an active home with someone who is around a good portion of the day (someone who works from home would be great) or in a home with a calm adult dog who could show him the ropes.

Medical information: Buddy is up to date on his shots, microchipped and in good overall health. He will be heartworm tested and neutered soon. 

Buddy is located in: San Jose
 
If you would like to have a great  Buddy in your life, please contact Rescue Rep Debbi at dragonflydebbi@gmail.com (preferred) or 408-309-7830.  Please read about teenage dogs here first to be sure you are up for a teenager:   

https://www.sciencemag.org/news/2020/05/dogs-get-difficult-when-they-reach-adolescence-just-human-teenagers

animal.description:
Hello! My name is Truck. I'm a 4-month-old Pitbull mix puppy with plenty of love and kisses to give. I enjoy playing with toys and other dogs, but I'm not too sure about cats.

I love a good cuddle with my people and prefer to sleep beside you at night rather than the crate. I'm a little protective of my food and bones, but with some training and care, this should get better!

As you may be able to see, my front legs (especially my left) are a little wonky! I had injuries to my legs as a small pup, but that does not stop me from running and playing. It will be important that my family understands that my legs may never be straight and that I need to keep a good lean weight.

I am very excited to go home to my new family and start new adventures! woot woot!

I am up to date on vaccinations, microchipped, heartworm negative, and neutered. 

My adoption fee is $300?

animal.description:
Medical adoption;

Please carefully read Violet's bio before applying
Unfit applicants and inquiries won't be responded to.

You can find the adoption process and the application on our website

straytoplay.org/adopt

Ideal home:  Violet is looking for an experienced owner(s) who has the time and patience to work on her issues. A home with no kids or other animals where she will be allowed on the furniture.

Name: Violet
Age: Estimated 4 years old
Weight: 15 lbs
Breed: Shih Tzu mix
Energy level: Medium
Good with dogs: Selective on leash, should be an only dog at home
Good with cats: Unknown, but not recommended. High prey drive
Good with kids: Adult-only home due to the bite history
Good with strangers: Very friendly but on her own terms
Guarding: Toys
Behavioral issues: Yes, bites as a defense mechanism in reaction to manipulations - wiping paws or putting on a jacket. Gives cues.
Housetrained: Yes
Cratetrained: Yes
Destructive: Not at all
Leash skills: Good for the most part, sometimes pulls
Medical issues: On October 25, Violet had bloodwork done at a vet visit and it was found that she had elevated liver enzymes. At this time, she was prescribed Denamarin and a prescription diet. At follow-up testing in December, her ALT level was down to normal range, but ALP was slightly elevated. Since there were improvements in the bloodwork, our vet recommended continuing the liver supplement and diet, and rechecking in a few months. Violet will be due for the next bloodwork in early March. At that point, if still elevated, then ultrasound is the next step to help to rule out major things like mass in the liver, gall bladder issues, cyst in the liver, or whether there is pancreatitis/enteritis etc.
If ALP levels have improved, we suspect the current medication/food would be a long-term requirement. (medication is approximately 70$/month and special food 30$/month)
The bloodwork in March and further screening (if required) is covered by the rescue if done at our partner vet - medication and food at the adopter's expense

animal.description:
What can we say about this amazing gentle boy?  He came to us injured with bite wounds from being attacked(?) - the shelter loved on him and knew how special he truly is. He is shy at first, unsure at first, but once he opens up (which is quick) he just wants to be your true companion - to give love and to be loved. We are working on a jumping up issue with him, which he just does to get your attention, as if to say “Hey, I’m right here and not done wanting some love from you”. He is quick to learn, and we are teaching him to sit to be pet and loved on instead of jumping up. His response time is awesome!  We have all fallen head over heels in love with this big boy, but we know, he truly needs his forever home, where he can be inside with his new person or family. He will truly be a great companion for that special person out there looking for that very special dog as that is what he is. He is one of a kind. His gentle touch when you pet him and stop for a moment, then he puts his paw on your hand to remind you that he is still there 

If you are looking for that special boy, that constant companion who is 100% LOVE, then our Rupert is your boy!  

He is approx 4 years old, Neutered, Vaccinated, Microchipped, Wormed and truly the best dog ever.  He has been in the play yard with another male dog and he just wants to play like a puppy. He is lower energy however - as he has matured past the puppy stage now, so he would do well with even an older person/couple. He is very good on a lead, so walking him is easy as well. He is patient, and like we have said, the purest form of love there is.  Not to mention how GORGEOUS he is!

animal.description:
Due to the current situation with the COVID-19 (Corona) virus, in-person home visits are not possible at this time. Since this is a very important part of finding the best home for our dogs, we are not accepting any applications from first-time pet owners, applicants who have not had a pet in the past 3 years, or applicants who cannot furnish vet records. We hope you understand and that you will consider applying to adopt once restrictions have been lifted. Liza Jane is a cute black Cocker Spaniel mix. She is approximately 9 years old and weighs 35-40 lbs. She’s up to date on all vaccinations and negative for HW. She has a very calm demeanor and loves to be scratched. She’s a true Velcro dog! She does very well at the dog park with all sizes and likes going on short walks since she is considered a senior. She is very food motivated, loves her treats, and clears her bowl every time. She is also crate trained, but needs a treat to get her inside. We were told if you push her into her crate, she might snap but not truly bite, so offering a treat works best. Liza Jane also enjoys being on the couch or her dog bed. At night she gets a little anxious so she prefers her crate with a blanket over it. When she’s lonely or anxious she will let you know by letting out a little howl. She would do best in a home with a family who is home a lot because she wants constant company. A family with older children would be best advised because she can be startled easily with sudden movement or loud noises. In addition, it would be best that she be the only dog since she loves constant attention. If you would like to meet Liza Jane, please complete our adoption application and put her name at the top. https://dfwcockerrescue.org/adoption-process/

For more pictures and information about this and all the cockers available at DFW Cocker Spaniel Rescue please visit our website at www.dfwcockerrescue.org

Name: DW
Breeds: Pit Bull Mix
Age: Puppy
Gender: Female

Hello, DW here taking applications to be your new snuggle buddy! DW was brought to the shelter as a younger pup by a Good Samaritan as she was found and not using one of her hind legs. The shelter took care of her and found out she had a fracture through one of the growth plates that is pretty common in puppies. This can happen due to jumping and landing wrong, falling from something etc. Their vet repaired the fracture, and because she was so young it has healed nicely and shouldn’t set her back at all in the future. She is great in her dog play group and has done well in foster homes with both dogs and cats. She has a great start to potty training, but expect to perfect this once she gets to MN. She is a love bug and is really looking forward to her forever home when she arrives on 2/6. All adoptions have a two week trial period. 

Requirements: Home with yard space. 

Adoption Fee: $475 + tax. This includes neuter/spay, current vaccinations as age appropriate, heartworm/tick testing if appropriate, deworming, microchip, and current preventatives

Interested in adopting?  Fill out a preadopt application here: https://form.jotform.com/203104997748162

You can email fostersheadinghomek9@gmail.com with additional questions.

This dog is located in Minneapolis, MN

animal.description:
Meet Milo! This handsome Retriever mix is looking for a home to call his own. Milo is an intelligent, active dog who loves to spend time with his people. This sweet boy enjoys filling his days going on long walks through the neighborhood, and romping around the backyard. He is a big fan of toys, and will happily play fetch with a tennis ball (though he isn't always so great about bringing them back yet!). 

Milo has great house manners, and is fully house trained. He rides well in the car, and makes an excellent errand running buddy! Milo loves to chew, and really enjoys having lots of hard chewing bones and toys around for him to entertain himself with each day. 

Milo is a sensitive soul who responds best to a person who will give him the time and patience needed to help boost his confidence. He can become worried about unexpected changes or new people in his environment, and needs a family ready to show him the world isn't a scary place. Tasty treats and gentle handling go a long ways in helping him feel comfortable. 

Milo enjoys the company of other dogs, and could do well in a home with another, confident dog to show him the ropes. He will do best in an adult only home, with a backyard for him to explore each day. This sweet guy is going to bring a lot of joy and happiness to his forever family. If Milo sounds like the right fit for your household, schedule an adoption appointment today.

animal.description:
Hi, I'm Masha!

Do you like other dogs? I do not have a good history with dogs and I need to be the only dog in the home.

What do you think about cats? I lived with an indoor cat and did well. But I did like to chase the cat for fun at times. So I would need a dog savvy cat with very slow and careful introductions. 

So how do you feel about kids? I did well around kids in my previous home. I can play rough at times, so I will need kids that can tolerate my play style. 

What is it that staff and volunteers love about you? I am a beautiful dilute brindle.

** Here is what a volunteer says about me:
"She is playful, smart and has lots of energy, but also enjoys quiet time." **

Is there anything else we should know about you? I am 6 years and 11months old and I weigh between 75-78lbs. I have a behavior waiver that the staff will discuss with you.

I came into the shelter as a stray and the above information is all recommendations based on my behavior seen at the shelter. I have no known history and it is very likely that I have not shown staff 100% of my personality. Expect to learn more about me after adoption.

It is unknown how this animal will do in their new home as all animals can be different with each person. It is important to take this into consideration when thinking about adopting and making sure you are prepared to work with any potential medical or behavior issues that occur after adoption.

My adoption fee includes my spay/neuter, current vaccinations, permanent microchip identification, certificate for a free veterinary exam, post-adoption support and more!
Thank you for taking the time to learn a little about me! If you think we would be a good match come on down and ask to meet me! I'm looking for my forever home and it could be with you!

ADOPTION INFORMATION: If you live in the city of Eugene or in Lane County you will be purchasing a dog license in addition to the adoption fee. You will get to choose between a one year, two year, or three year license. 
This pet is located at Greenhill Humane Society. 88530 Greenhill Road Eugene, OR 97402 (541) 689-1503. See all of the pets at this shelter by visiting www.green-hill.org.

Hi there! I was recently rescued by National Mill Dog Rescue, and my dedicated care team is still learning all about me. The intake team said I am scared. Please check back soon to read my biography. Meanwhile you can learn more about the organization that rescued me here: http://nmdr.org
 - - - - - -
Prior to being rescued, many of our dogs have experienced minimal socialization. As a result, there is often an adjustment period when learning about life as a family pet. We typically do not adopt dogs to homes with young children. Homes with older children will be considered on an individual basis. Common skills such as house training and leash walking will often take a little extra time. Patience, understanding and a gentle hand are a must. The great news is, most of these dogs come around rather quickly and being a part of their rehabilitation is an extremely rewarding experience. Learn about mill dogs and fill out an application at our website: http://nmdr.org

MY NAME IS:  Daisy
POSTED TO PETFINDER DATE:  Jan 25, 2021
SIZE: 58 pounds
APPROXIMATE AGE: 3 years
SHELTER STAFF SAYS:  A daisy conveys innocence, loyal love, and purity. Our sweet Daisy embodies all that and more! She is the most lovable girl you will ever meet, and she is looking for her furever home! She will need a little work on leash, but is SO smart that it won't take her long. Daisy's ears are going to need a little extra attention, but she is worth it and more. Come on out and meet this lovely flower, and you will have to pluck her right up! Daisy can't wait to meet you, and she says, " Happiness blooms from within, and spreads without!"

Due to Covid, we now work by appointment only and work on a first come basis.  If you are interested in making an appointment, please call the HCHS at 512-793-5463.  You can see all our available animals at HillCountryHumaneSociety.org.
All our adoptable dogs are treated for fleas, given DHPPV and Bordatella vaccines and are de-wormed.  
When you adopt one of our animals it will be micro chipped and registered at the time of adoption.  Also, if not already altered, you will receive a voucher to get your animal spay/neutered.
While we do our best to determine the breeds of our dogs, the majority are strays, and we have only general appearance, coat type, size, ear type, tail, tongue color and coat color to base breed on.  It is always possible when adopting a puppy that it will change dramatically to look like another breed.

animal.description:
**WE ARE CURRENTLY DOING ADOPTIONS BY APPOINTMENT ONLY. YOU MUST CALL TO SCHEDULE AN APPOINTMENT IF YOU'RE INTERESTED IN ADOPTING. PLEASE LEAVE US A VOICEMAIL IF YOU ARE UNABLE TO REACH US. THANK YOU FOR YOUR PATIENCE AND UNDERSTANDING.- CCDP STAFF**

Hi there. My name is Noodle Bandit (Bandit). I'm about 1 year old and I weigh about 55 lbs. 
I am a sweet boy looking for a loving family. 
I am very energetic and will need a new family that can give me plenty of exercise. 
I will also need a little work with manners, but I am very smart and I pick up on things very quickly. I am good in my kennel and appear to be housebroken. 
I get along well with most other dogs and I like to play. 
If you're looking for a sweet dog to add to your family, please consider adopting me.

Our adoption fee is $150.00. The pound DOES NOT accept checks for adoption fees. We're able to accept cash for adoption OR Visa/ Mastercard/ Discover Card. A convenience fee of 2.39% will be applied to all credit/ debit card adoptions. If you intend to do a foster-to-adopt, the fee must be cash. ALL dogs/puppies adopted from our shelter will receive their parvo distemper vaccine, bordetella vaccine, rabies vaccine (if aged at 12 weeks or older), be dewormed with a 3 day course of panacur dewormer, be microchipped, receive their current Ohio dog license and will be spayed or neutered. ALL DOGS/PUPPIES WILL BE SPAYED OR NEUTERED unless a health issue prohibits the surgery from being performed. Not all dogs posted for adoption are spayed/ neutered yet. If you're driving a long distance to adopt, please verify that the vetting process has been completed and dog you're interested in adopting is still available for adoption. The above mentioned vetting is all included in your adoption fee. The adoption fee and what is included in the adoption fee is NON-NEGOTIABLE.

Adoptions MUST be done at the pound and in person as there is paperwork to fill out and an adoption contract that must be signed by the adopter. This means you must be willing to travel to our shelter to adopt.

IF the dog you're interested in adopting has medical conditions or injuries which require medical treatment, we ask that you help with the medical bills so we can continue to help the dogs coming in who need additional vet care.
We are a county run shelter, therefore we cannot control our intake or the health or behavior of the dogs that come in to our shelter.

Although we try our hardest to place all of our adoptable dogs, there are certain circumstances in which any dog in our care could be euthanized at any time and without further notice (IE: sudden untreatable medical condition or injury, temperament or behavioral problems which may not be apparent when the dog first arrives, lack or space, etc.), therefore all dogs at our shelter should be considered urgent. The adoption of a more highly adoptable dog will mean more time for the less adoptable dog in the kennel next to him!

Shelter hours are: Monday-Friday: 8 am- 4 pm
Saturday: 8 am - 11 am.
Sunday: 8 am - 11 am.
Adoptions are always welcome during hours of operation. We will make special arrangements for adoptions in advance.
There is nobody in the office on Saturday and Sunday, so therefore we are unable to answer or return phone calls over the weekend.

Can't adopt a dog? We would love to have more volunteers who are able to spend time with our dogs! The dogs LOVE going for walks and the socialization and exercise helps make the dogs more adoptable.

Contact information:
8455 County Home Road
Lisbon, OH 44432
(330)424-6663
Email: hpecorelli@ccclerk.org

Intake date: 1/22/2020
Intake type: Surrender

Home with other dogs: Yes but nobody too crazy- I tend to get nervous with other dogs that can be a little crazy

Home with children: Over the age 10
Home with cats: No

Crate trained & Housebroken: Yes

I am very treat motivated which makes me easy to train. My shelter family has already started working with me on manners since I came to the shelter and Iv already gotten much better. Have I mentioned that I love giving big wet, sloppy, kisses :) 

If you think I'm the right doggo for you, please submit an adoption application!

The dog you have selected is a Belgian Malinois.  This is a breed that has very specific needs for an adoptive home.  Because of their need for a high level of exercise, both mentally and physically and their need for ongoing training, only applicants with demonstrated owner/handler experience with this breed will be considered. animal.description:
CINDER AND DESTINY:  BONDED FOR LIFE

Cinder and Destiny are bonded for life. They are both incredibly gentle and sweet, sweeter than chocolate cake with buttercream icing. Cinder is a Lab/Shepherd female and she is 10 years young and full of life. Destiny is a Catahoula/Lab female, 7 years young and full of sunshine. They are both so beautiful and full of grace. Cinder and Destiny arrived from Texas after they suffered a huge loss in their life when they lost their beloved Mom to cancer. They have been grieving her loss, but are hoping you can help them heal and mend their broken hearts. Everyone that has met them has fallen head over heals with their sweet and kind heart, and overall adorableness. They are easy going, housetrained, leash trained, and enjoy car rides. They were once cherished family members, and LaMancha’s promise to them is to find them a loving family who will cherish them for the rest of their life. Please don’t let their age deter you, they are fabulous girls who are full of life. Cinder and Destiny just want the simple things in life, love and loyalty. Afterall, they are the most extraordinary things in life.  

We know if you come meet them, you will fall in love with them in a zeptosecond, just like all the volunteers and their entire rescue team have done.

To give Cinder and Destiny your last name and make them a cherished family member, please email Rescue@LamanchaAnimalRescue.org  and write Cinder and Density in the subject line. 





Spayed, UTD vaccinations, chipped, wormed.

Housetrained.

animal.description:
Buck is 1-2 year old shepherd mix who is looking for a forever family! He’s a 57lb ball of energy with all the love in the world to give!
As a result of living chained outside by previous owners he is unfortunately heartworm positive, but it is treatable and covered by the rescue.  He’s also current on vaccines, neutered, housebroken, kennel trained, and microchipped. 
He’s friendly towards everyone but would be better suited in a house with older children. 
Buck is a great car rider and would do best with a family that participates in dog friendly activities that he’d be included in to help him expend his puppy energy. Currently, he is receiving training and knows “sit” and “down” continued training will be necessary to manage some of his impulsive behaviors. 
Buck is very friendly towards other dogs but cats may find his higher energy level overwhelming. 
You really couldn’t find a more affectionate boy who wants nothing more than your love and attention!

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

The adoption fee for adult dogs covers age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, spay/neuter if not yet performed, heartworm test & appropriate heartworm treatment by the rescue's vet. All dogs in our care are also kept up-to-date on HW/Flea Prevention. Please see our website for more information. 

2021 Adoption Fee Scale for non-benefactor animals:
Puppies under 12 months - $300
Dogs over 12 months - $200

For additional information, including the adoption process and our adoption fee scale for all our adoptable pets, see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

*Any breed labels used by Take Paws Rescue, its employees/volunteers, or on vet records provided cannot be guaranteed.  Breed labels are given based on information obtained during intake and/or best guesses based on appearance and/or temperament of the dogs and Take Paws Rescue gives no assurance to the accuracy of these labels. Labels are necessary for postings to many animal networking sites, such as Pet Finder, and are no way a guarantee. Additionally, exact age and potential size cannot be guaranteed.

animal.description: Titan is a 2 - 3 yr old male Pitbull. He is a loose and wiggly guy who loves to give kisses. He is very high energy, so we recommend a home with older children. He pulls on a leash, but this can be resolved with obedience training. Titan is food motivated, and knows the commands sit and down. He is intensely interested in cats in the shelter environment. Dogs are generally tested with dogs of their own size; and dog meets with the resident dogs are always encouraged. Our cat test should be used as a general purpose screening only to rule out overt aggression; we always recommend caution when introducing dogs to cats in the home. Recommendation on suitability of placement with children by their ages is based on behavioral observations including energy level and response to body handling. We never recommend leaving young children unsupervised with dogs, and we cannot guarantee the behavior of dogs with children, other pets or cats. Behavior evaluations should be considered as a snapshot of the behavior of the dog at this point in time; JHS believes all dog families need to be prepared to invest time and energy into training as well as provide common sense management of their new dog. We always encourage family to do some research on the breeds or mixes of breeds prior to adoption as many can have some unique characteristics that may or may not fit into their families. Always remember that the majority of dogs at our shelter have been exposed to or may have kennel cough. Kennel cough is contagious to other dogs, please talk to your vet if you have any questions about kennel cough prior to adoption. Please ask your adoption counselor at time of adoption if you have any unanswered questions regarding illnesses and treatments of the path that you are adopting. For more information about this dog or any others at our Shelter, please visit www.joplinhumane.org. We are the Joplin Humane Society in Joplin, Missouri. 417-623-3642. I AM SPONSORED! Thank you Darcy Robison for sponsoring me!

animal.description:
Tuco (Black/White) and Blondie (Tan/White) are 5 year old brothers who would love to find a home together. They were born on 04/20/2015. Their previous owner is not able to provide them the time that they need for their energy level.

Just like your typical JRT, these two are VERY energetic and have a high drive for fun!!! They are always on the go and love to play chase, wrestle, and hunt for critters! They are just about house trained, they are crate trained, EXTREMELY obedient and is always eager to please and learn new things. They are super duper sweet and friendly and loves all people, including children but because they have a tendency to get exuberant, excited, and will jump up, we recommend older children (13+) only in the household rather than toddlers and young children. They would love to have a family who will include them in your life and take them on adventures with you. But when they are not loving on you or out and about, they are entertaining themselves by playing a game of chase in the yard or catching lizards. They are great with other dogs but prefer mellow dogs rather than large rambunctious puppies and young adults. And even though they do have high motors going, at the end of the day they are quite content being lap dogs and binge watching the lastest Netflix series!

If interested in ADOPTING, please fill out an adoption application online:
www.hoperanchanimalsanctuary.org/adoption-application

A copy of your application can be sent to us via email

For more information about Tuco and Blondie, please contact Sandra:
Call/Text: (760) 585-5973
Email: sandrahoperanch@gmail.com

animal.description:
Meet Leo, the youngest pup to join Grey Face Rescue! Leo is looking for a very active family that can keep up with him! He is also hoping for an active puppy playmate. We can't pinpoint his breed - he was transferred to us as a Great Dane mix but we quickly learned that he is definitely in the hound family. He loves playing and running around with other dogs so we are looking for a home with another dog that is as active as Leo. He should not go to a home with cats or small dogs, as he is very high prey drive. He would do great with older kids! He is still a puppy so he's a bit mouthy - he would benefit from some additional training.

Do you need a running buddy? Does your dog need a friend? If so, Leo is the puppy you need!

Age: 1-year-old

Breed: Hound Mix (possibly Great Dane)

Weight: 60+ lbs

Kid-friendly: He is still very much puppy and mouthy so we wouldn't recommend small children. He does great with teenagers.

Dogs: Leo does a great job with playing with other big dogs! He is interested in dogs on walks, but will keep walking after a sniff. We do not recommend living with small dogs due to his prey drive.

Cats: We don't recommend cats.

Crate trained: Yes! Leo currently gets crated at night or while his foster is out running errands. He also chooses to go in his crate for naps. He doesn't like to be crated when there is activity in the house.

Potty trained: He can go at least 4 hours without having accidents. He gets up once in the night to potty, but we think he could hold it for longer!

Likes: This big puppy has a lot of energy and loves to run, play, and go to the dog park! Leo loves to chew on bones, typically knuckle bones, filled with peanut butter. Leo loves to play with other dogs. He also loves chewing on squeaky toys. Leo loves to cuddle when he's tired too.

Health concerns: None

Adoption fee: $425

Adopters will be responsible for continued preventatives, follow-up appointments, and medications (if applicable).

$50 discount for seniors (65+) and veterans. Adoption fees help pay for the dog's veterinary exam, vaccinations (rabies, distemper, and bordetella), HW test, blood panel, a microchip, and spay/neuter if needed and additional health needs specific to each animal.

animal.description:
Nessa came to rescue as an owner surrender. HER DOB is 11.24.18 and her adoption fee is $350.00.  She will be spay soon as appointments have been a little slow to get because of COVID.

She is very sweet, loveable, house broken but not trustworthy off leash in an unfenced area. Her foster dad has been taking her out on a 50' leash and letting her get exercise in a country setting.   She is good on a long leash and never pulls but could use some obedience training classes to learn to walk beside someone.  She is excited about horses and other small animals. We do not recommend a home with small animals, such as cats or bunnies or horses.  She gets along currently with a male and female German Shepherd and recommend she be placed with a male dog for a permanent FUREVER home.  She is housebroken but may have an accident in a new home and will need to be watched so she can learn the signals to go out.  

She  is always friendly, gives lots of kisses, cuddles and does love to play with bones and toys.  She has learned :the following: sit, wait, stay.  You can not leave her loose over night or she may have an accident or get in to things she should .  She loves toys, bones, jolly balls or all balls.  She does not want to do a down but we think it will happen in time.

She loves car rides but has not visited any stores currently.  She has an excellent recall.  If you are serious about this beautiful Shepherd please fill out an application at www.faerielandrescue.org under resources.

animal.description: Are you one of those people that loves surprises? Well, I am the perfect pooch for you! With my ordinary name and less than stellar good looks, I am that perfect package waiting to show that special someone how amazing I am! I was brought to the shelter by my owners as they couldn't provide me desperately needed veterinary care. They assumed I had no hope left of recovery. Fortunately the shelter team realized I just needed some minor veterinary treatment, special baths, a nutritious diet and some love! After only a short time, I am already showing so much improvement! I am a pretty easy going boy (as long as I get enough physical and mental exercise!) that is looking for a family that will continue to help me heal and show me what indoor living is like! I am housebroken, crate trained and I ride well in a car. I enjoy jumping up on people (I am working on that), pulling on leash and checking out what my people keep on counter tops. I get along with other dogs and enjoy brief romps in the yard with them and my prior owners reported I lived with cats. While I am putting on weight and recovery from a noncontagious mange, I am heartworm negative and will need to continue having regular conditioning baths (which I adore!). I am eager to please, smart, food and toy motivated and looking for someone to teach me about the finer things in life. I would do best in a home without young kids and that can continue to provide me a good routine. If you are looking for a well rounded boy that is just looking for some training, adventure and companionship, please make arrangements to meet me!

animal.description: Ever seen a hippo wiggle? Meet Akira and you probably will. This roly-poly momma is sweet as can be. She's generally very low-key and easygoing, but when she's excited or happy to see you, you'll know it by her signature whole-body shimmy. Akira is excellent on leash and a great partner for a leisurely walk. She likes to stop and check in every once in a while, happily accepting a scratch under her collar before you continue on your way. Children make Akira a little nervous, so she needs a home without children under 12. She has done well with male dogs, but likes to be the only lady. Because she is classified as a pitbull, her home will need to have a fenced in yard (or reside in Sarpy County), so no apartments for her. If you have a quieter home and a love for dog cuddles, then Akira is your gal! Akira will be shown by appointment only. If you are interested in learning more about this animal, please fill out an application by clicking here . Be sure to include Akira A1085204 when filling out the survey. After reviewing your application, we will only be reaching out to you if the animal is a good fit for your home.

animal.description:
Colin Bridgerton is a black fluffy male lab/shepherd mix. He has a touch of white on his chest and will grow up to be a large beautiful dog. His birthday was 12/16. He will be vaccinated and microchipped this week once he is 6 weeks old. He loves to play and wrestle with his brother, then cuddle and nap. They do great in the kennel and sleep through the night. Potty training is also going well for their age! This sweetheart is ready for a forever home!

Please note: as with most rescue puppies, we have no way to guarantee this puppy’s breed or size potential. 

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

The adoption fee for adult dogs covers age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, spay/neuter if not yet performed, heartworm test & appropriate heartworm treatment by the rescue's vet. All dogs in our care are also kept up-to-date on HW/Flea Prevention. Please see our website for more information. 

2021 Adoption Fee Scale for non-benefactor animals:
Puppies under 12 months - $300
Dogs over 12 months - $200

For additional information, including the adoption process and our adoption fee scale for all our adoptable pets, see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

*Any breed labels used by Take Paws Rescue, its employees/volunteers, or on vet records provided cannot be guaranteed.  Breed labels are given based on information obtained during intake and/or best guesses based on appearance and/or temperament of the dogs and Take Paws Rescue gives no assurance to the accuracy of these labels. Labels are necessary for postings to many animal networking sites, such as Pet Finder, and are no way a guarantee. Additionally, exact age and potential size cannot be guaranteed.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
Name: DakotaRae
DOB: 11/19/2018
Weight: 75 pounds
Adoption Fee: $375

I'm a proud and dedicated recent momma who is looking for the next step! I'm ready to be an empty nester and am looking for a family that will provide me with plenty of head scratches and belly rubs, comfy places to nap, and long sniffy walks. I enjoy getting out of the house and exploring, whether it's jumping into piles of snow or taking a long stroll around the neighborhood. Sometimes I push the pace on walks (between good sniffing spots of course!), so I think I would enjoy running.

I love to nap and have claimed all areas of the house as my bed - why settle for only one? While I love my beauty sleep and relaxation, I choose to cuddle only when I'm in the mood. This makes my foster momma treat me extra special when I lay my head on her lap :) I've recently discovered this thing called "toys", and I love pouncing and playing with them. Additionally, I noticed that shoes and slippers look a lot like my toys and I really like to carry them around.

I protect the house and yard from intruders and voice an alarm when I see people walking by or hear weird sounds. I might be less protective once I don't have ten pups to worry about. I'm house trained and lay by the front door to ask to go outside. I'm crate trained and snooze in there overnight without a peep. During the day, I'm trusted to be free roam in most of the house, though I'm rarely alone. I "sit" and "touch" for treats and am eager to learn more, as long as yummy snacks are involved. I get along well with other dogs as long as we're introduced slowly and do well on car rides.

In the meantime if you have questions or are interested in me, please fill out an adoption application at www.ruffstartrescue.org.

An adoption application is the best way to show your interest in an animal. Please check out our website, www.ruffstartrescue.org for more details and additional pictures on any of our animals! All Ruff Start dogs and cats are spayed/neutered, up to date on age appropriate vaccines, microchipped, dewormed, and on monthly flea/tick and heartworm prevention (dogs) as well as heartworm tested (dogs). Ruff Start Rescue is a foster based rescue. Animals are located in homes throughout Minnesota. We do not have a facility where animals are kept. Ruff Start Rescue Adoption Policies: http://www.ruffstartrescue.org/info/display?PageID=11744

animal.description:
Those eyes, we know!!!  So stunning!  This is Joey, a 2 year old male Husky/Labrador mix.  He has a thick golden-red and white coat with those husky ice blue eyes.  Joey is a big dog weighing 56 pounds and this is full grown.  Joey was pulled from our local animal shelter where he had been picked up as a stray and down there for several weeks with no on coming to claim him.  

Joey is a little shy at first but warms up quickly to give you a kiss on the cheek.  He is like a big puppy in many ways: loves to run and romp around and loves to play with his toys.  We feel he may be too big for an apartment and would be much better suited to a place with a fenced in yard so he can have room to run and play. Plus Joey has no clue what to do on a leash and sometimes has to be carried places.  He will need some leash training!  He is not to be an outside dog only, Joey loves to be with his people too much.  Joey did well with the animals he has been around and should be fine with children 8 and over, just not real young kids he might accidentally bump over.  

We have started on his crate training.  Joey is up to date on his vet care, will be neutered prior to adoption, heartworm negative and microchipped.  He is on heartworm and flea/tick prevention.
Such a unique looking dog with lots of love to give – what more could you ask for when looking for your new buddy!!

All HSWA dogs are either at our Dog Adoption Facility or in foster homes. All dogs require an appointment to meet.  Please call us at 205-554-0011 or email humaneswa@yahoo.com to request an appointment to see the dog/puppy and to check availability.

Visit us on Facebook! www.facebook.com/humaneswa

Our adoption fee is $75.  Read more information on our adoption process at www.humanesocietyofwa.org/howtoadopt.html.  Then, if you feel your home might be the right forever home and you would like to adopt a dog, submit an online adoption application. The online applications may not work on mobile devices. If the online application does not work on your device, look to the right side of the forms page for a downloadable .PDF copy of the application.

animal.description: Up last is our largest black and white dog from this trip. Doesn't he look debonair in his tuxedo? Scotty is a one-year-old Terrier/Mix who is ready for love and we're hoping he's looking in all the right place. With that face, we're not worried. Scotty is one of our largest dogs at almost fifty-pounds so if you like big guys he's an obvious pick. After a doggy obedience class and some boundaries, Scotty is going to fit right in. Scotty enjoys playing with other dogs so far, has his eye on a few toys as he decides which are "his and so far, he gets along well with people. Scotty has no restrictions as far as future living situations other than that he'll need walks and play to keep him happy. If you are up for a fun frolic around town and then a sweet snuggle afterward you'll want to come and meet Scotty as soon as possible. Scotty is up to date on vaccinations, neutered, and will be microchipped so if you like large dogs with extra love to give then please come and meet Scotty soon. animal.description:
**SPECIAL CASE**
Meet Bumbles!
Bumbles is an approx 9-10 mth old Tennessee Mountain Cur who previously belonged to someone who loved him dearly but was unable to care for Bumbles.  Bumbles developed a severe case of demodex (non contagious) mange and a secondary bacterial skin infection.  He was underweight and in such bad condition that his face was extremely painful and a very bloody, oozing mess.  It has taken 6 weeks of intense vet care and medications,baths and TLC but Bumbles has turned a corner and is looking GREAT. 
We will consider an experienced adopter or a 4 week foster-to-adopt period with local adopters to complete his follow up care.
Bumbles has had limited contact with other dogs while in our care.  He can get a bit overexcited with them still.  He can also be a bit scared of new people but is a silly, snuggly puppy with those he trusts.  
He would benefit from a family willing to help get him acclimated and start working on the training and socialization that he has missed out on.  He promises to reward your time and love with his loyalty.  He has *so* much potential that just has not been realized.  The last 6 weeks he has already started to blossom.  Bumbles loves peanut butter and being told how handsome he is.  
Bumbles' adoption fee includes his neuter, vaccinations, vet care to date and heartworm testing (negative).  If you are looking to give a deserving dog a chance, Bumbles is your guy!
Interested?  Email us at dtradoptions@gmail.com with details about your home/family and environment or complete an application at www.dogtownrescue.org

animal.description: Roscoe came to us several weeks ago from a very difficult situation in which he did have not much socialization. The staff and volunteers have been working with him to gain his trust and help socialize him to the best of his ability. At the golden age of seven years, Roscoe is now looking for a solid foundation in a calm, patient household. He is more fond of women, so a strong female leader is something that would do him justice. Ongoing socialization, daily routine, and decompression time would highly benefit him in his new home. We are unsure how he feels about other dogs, so dogs are required to do a supervised visit prior to adoption. He would do best in a home with adults only. He did previously live with another dog and cats. If placed again with cats, we ask for a very slow, well-managed introduction. Roscoe walks well on leash, knows sit, stay and shake! If a golden senior that really deserves a second chance is something you're looking for, Roscoe may be the fella for you!

animal.description:
Howdy, Cash here!
Im an Oklahoma native, recently coming to Kansas City when my last shelter ran out of room. Ive heard great things about Kansas City so I cant wait to see what all the hype is about when my forever family finds me and takes me home! At 48 pounds, I am the perfect combination of fun and explorative as well as a great cuddle buddy!
People here at Wayside say that I am a friendly, outgoing guy who loves to be close to people. I have been known to weave in and out of legs so I will definitely keep my new family on their toes (otherwise you might trip, ha!). I am a wiggly guy too who loves pets. When I see some of my favorite people coming down my row my whole body just wiggles and wiggles! I can't wait to hang out with them!
Iam treat/praise motivated. I love to learn new things! I am currently enrolled in a training program at the shelter where I am learning all sorts of new things. So far I know how to sit, lay down, and give a nose touch.I love to play with toys and enjoy going on walks. I also love to play with other dogs in play groups here at Wayside!
Recently, I got to participate in Waysides Waifs Day Out program where a nice volunteer took me outside the shelter to explore the city. It was so amazing! In fact, I even got a new toy and it was really the best day ever.
I cant wait to meet you and see if we could be the perfect match for each other!
See you soon!
Cash

animal.description:
Queue the 80s music station.. We are the champions, my friend! All kidding aside, did you know that Noland is an Irish name for champion? Well, we have a champion cuddler given the right opportunity! Noland is a pittie, smushy face mix around 2 years old and 52 lbs. He's a friendly boy who makes friends quickly and loves his playtime with the group mates. Strong and athletic, Noland will do best in an active family setting where he can join jogs, be your walking partner or whatever to keep you moving. Other dogs or kids would be fine with him or he'd be OK as your one and only. Noland loves being with people and will happily be your oversized lap dog.
He was great in the car, great on a leash, happily sleeps in his crate at night, and not very talkative
. While he doesn't know too many tricks or commands, he responds quickly to corrections.
His good looks can't be completely captured in a photo, so click over to send in an application to meet Noland and he'll meet you at the gate!

animal.description:
Cooper here. Thanks for clicking on my picture so I can tell you a little about myself. I'm a handsome boy if I do say so myself. I'm around 5 years old and I'm done with puppyhood, but I still like to have a good time playing with friends. I had a nice home once and would really like to get back to the movie watching, couch napping world that I had before. I like to exercise regularly to keep myself healthy, but no need to go all out with a full out running schedule. I wouldn't mind being your only dog, but other girl dogs in your house would be fine with me. Kids are certainly welcome too! I don't mind being a work from home partner either and will sit quietly during your conference calls. If you sit down on the floor with me I'll come over and nuzzle my head into your neck to give you a loving hug. If it's okay with you, I'd love to snuggle up in bed at night if I'm invited first. I know to go potty outside, and I don't mind being brushed.
I'd love to meet you if I sound like your kind of guy. I can be reached by sending an application to Saving Grace and scheduling an appointment. Hope to see you soon!
